# <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">How to setup Google Tag Manager</span></span>

> <div class="sd-callout" data-callout-type="info"><strong>PLEASE NOTE:</strong> This only applies if you do not want to use our auto-blocking feature. Otherwise follow the instructions here</div>
> 
> <div class="sd-callout" data-callout-type="alert">Before proceeding please <strong>remove/deactivate any existing scripts/plugins you may have previously used to integrate TRUENDO</strong> on your website. Google Tag manager will do it automatically once the procedure below is completed.</div>

## Google Tag Manager Without Consent Mode Enabled

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Here you’ll find a step-by-step guide for setting up Google Tag Manager in combination with TRUENDO.</span></span>

### <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Step 1</span></span>

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Download our Tag Manager JSON file. This file contains the necessary tags, triggers and variables to make TRUENDO work with the Google Tag Manager.</span></span>

[<span style="color:rgb(0, 85, 187);"><span style="background-color:transparent;">Download TRUENDO-GTM JSON</span></span>](https://truendo-file-hosting.s3.eu-central-1.amazonaws.com/TRUENDO-GTM.json)

### <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Step 2</span></span>

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Now import the file to the Workspace.</span></span>

1.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Log in to your Google Tag manager account and click the </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Admin</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Tab, then click on the </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Import Container</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">option from the panel on the right.</span></span>
    
    <br />
    
    <img src="https://app.snazzydocs.com/storage/users/hEfI2V55cVTdM5ty/docs/G2IomO8914MUXZZJ/images/LL8nfPN02tBldqcyX7aQ.png" alt="">
    
    <br />
    
2.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Then upload the </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">TRUENDO-GTM.json</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">file you downloaded before.</span></span>
3.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Set the Workspace to </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Default Workspace</span></span>**<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">.</span></span>
4.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Set the import options to </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Merge</span></span>**<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">.</span></span>
    
    <br />
    
    <div class="sd-callout" data-callout-type="info"><strong>Important Note</strong>: Do NOT set your import options to Overwrite. This would remove all your existing tags, triggers and variables.</div>
    
5.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Click </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Confirm</span></span>**<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">.</span></span>

<figure><img src="https://app.snazzydocs.com/storage/users/hEfI2V55cVTdM5ty/docs/G2IomO8914MUXZZJ/images/tHK6FDbqdjwNew4BBdO4.png"></figure>

<br />

### <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Step 3</span></span>

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Now you need to add your Site ID to the TRUENDO tag.</span></span>

1.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Log in to the TRUENDO </span></span> [<span style="color:rgb(0, 85, 187);"><span style="background-color:transparent;">Console</span></span>](https://console.truendo.com/), (select the correct Organization and website if you have more than one) then click **Banner** in the panel on the left of the screen, now scroll until you see **Integration via script**.
2.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Click </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Copy Site ID</span></span>**<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">.</span></span>
3.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Back in Google Tag Manager under the Tags tab, open the </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">TRUENDO</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">tag.</span></span>
4.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Now replace </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">YOUR WEBSITE ID</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">text (found near the bottom of the code block) with the ID you copied from the console, simply highlight and paste. Do not delete/replace the quotation marks.</span></span>
5.  Click **Save** and close the tag.
    
    <figure><img src="https://app.snazzydocs.com/storage/users/hEfI2V55cVTdM5ty/docs/G2IomO8914MUXZZJ/images/hsAbYFmrOjSG4Y2ULfKG.png"></figure>
    

### <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Step 4 - Tags and Specific Event Triggers</span></span>

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Some tags may have triggers that fire at specific events (e.g.: a tag that fires on certain scroll depths), as opposed to on every page. In such cases you need to connect those events with TRUENDO’s categories. To do that, each </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Trigger</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">must have an additional condition to only fire when the TRUENDO category is set to </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">true</span></span>**<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">.</span></span>

1.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Go to </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Triggers</span></span>**<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">.</span></span>
2.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Click on the trigger needing modification, then click edit (the pencil next to the trigger name) and set 'This trigger fires on'</span></span> <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">to </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Some Custom Events</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">or </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Some Pages</span></span>** depending on the trigger type<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">.</span></span>
3.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Then set the condition to: </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">TruendoCookie</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">&gt; </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">contains</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">&gt; </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">"[category]":true</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">and press </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Save</span></span>**<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">. Where category best describes tag triggered. For more info on the TRUENDO categories click </span></span> [<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">here</span></span>](http:#?target=0EB-94M4-TBP-GIU)<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">.</span></span>

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Example:</span></span>

**<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">TruendoCookie</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">&gt; </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">contains</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">&gt; </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">“statistics”:true</span></span>**

<figure><img src="https://app.snazzydocs.com/storage/users/hEfI2V55cVTdM5ty/docs/G2IomO8914MUXZZJ/images/uDhoi1TpNlwGv2VbRWgi.jpg"></figure>

<br />

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Do points 1-3 for every relevant trigger on the list.</span></span>

### <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Step 5 - Applying TRUENDO Triggers to other tags</span></span>

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">The last step is applying the TRUENDO triggers to the other tags (e.g. Google Analytics, Hotjar, Outbrain, etc.) you want to control. Every tag that is triggered on all pages gets the TRUENDO trigger that applies to its specific TRUENDO category.</span></span>

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">To do this add the Custom Event trigger (each trigger has the name </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Truendo</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">before its category) of the proper category to the trigger section. Make sure that the TRUENDO trigger is the only trigger in the tag, i.e. remove any other triggers.</span></span>

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Tags that use special events (Step 4 above) retain those triggers, since we have modified those to work with TRUENDO.</span></span>

## <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Can I set scripts in GTM and outside of GTM at the same time</span></span>

**<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Answer:</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Yes, you can. However make sure that Google Tag Manager is the first script that is being loaded on the website. The scripts outside of GTM still have to be set according to the </span></span> [<span style="color:rgb(0, 85, 187);"><span style="background-color:transparent;">documentation</span></span>](https://docs.truendo.com/docs/connect-cookies-to-the-privacy-panel/scripts/).

## <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">How to setup Hubspot with TRUENDO in Google Tag Manager</span></span>

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Some services might need some extra attention to be set up properly. Hubspot is one of these cases. In order to use Hubspot properly we have to let it set its cookie but only allow tracking if the User consents to it. There are only a few steps to follow.</span></span>

1.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Go to the TRUENDO tag in the Tag Manager.</span></span>
2.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Replace all the code with the following:</span></span>
    
    ```html
    &lt;script&gt;
    function TruendoCookieControlCallback(cookieObj) {
      if (cookieObj.preferences) {
         dataLayer.push({'event':'truendo_cc_preferences'});
      }
      if (cookieObj.marketing) {
        dataLayer.push({'event':'truendo_cc_marketing'});
      }
      if (cookieObj.statistics) {
        dataLayer.push({'event':'truendo_cc_statistics'});
        _hsq.push(['doNotTrack', {track: true}]); // Enable Hubspot tracking
      } else {
        _hsq.push(['doNotTrack']); // Disable Hubspot tracking
      }
      if (cookieObj.social_content){
        dataLayer.push({'event':'truendo_cc_social_content'});
      }
    }
    &lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script async="" id="truendoPrivacyPanel" type="text/javascript" src="https://cdn.priv.center/pc/app.pid.js" data-siteid="YOUR WEBSITE ID"&gt;
    &lt;/script&gt;
    ```
    
    > <div class="sd-callout" data-callout-type="info"><strong>Important Note:</strong> Make Sure that your replace the data-siteid with the one of your domain. You can find your Site ID in the TRUENDO Console. Under the <strong>Banner</strong> section scroll until you see <strong>Integration via script</strong>. You can simply click Copy Site ID</div>
    > 
    > <br />
    > 
    > <br />
    
3.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Remove the </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">async</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">attribute from your </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Hubspot</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">script.</span></span>
4.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Add a standard trigger to your </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Hubspot</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">tag. For example the </span></span> _<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">All Pages</span></span>_ <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">trigger.</span></span>

<br />

## <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">How to setup Hubspot with TRUENDO in </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(26, 26, 26) !important;"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Google Tag Manager With Consent Mode Enabled</span></span>**

<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Some services might need some extra attention to be set up properly. Hubspot is one of these cases. In order to use Hubspot properly we have to let it set its cookie but only allow tracking if the User consents to it. There are only a few steps to follow.</span></span>

1.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Go to the TRUENDO tag in the Tag Manager.</span></span>
2.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Replace all the code with the following:</span></span>
    
    ```html
    &lt;script&gt;
        window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
        function gtag() {
          dataLayer.push(arguments);
        }
    
        // set „denied' as default for both ad and analytics storage,
        gtag("consent", "default", {
          ad_storage: "denied",
          ad_user_data: "denied",
          ad_personalization: "denied",
          analytics_storage: "denied",
          preferences: "denied",
          social_content: "denied",
          social_sharing: "denied",
          wait_for_update: 500, // milliseconds to wait for update
        });
    
        // Enable ads data redaction by default [optional]
        gtag("set", "ads_data_redaction", true);
    
        function TruendoCookieControlCallback(cookieObj) {
          if (cookieObj.preferences) {
            gtag("consent", "update", {
              preferences: "granted",
            });
            dataLayer.push({ event: "truendo_cc_preferences" });
          } else {
            gtag("consent", "update", {
              preferences: "denied",
            });
          }
          if (cookieObj.marketing) {
            gtag("consent", "update", {
              ad_storage: "granted",
              ad_user_data: "granted",
              ad_personalization: "granted",
            });
            dataLayer.push({ event: "truendo_cc_marketing" });
          } else {
            gtag("consent", "update", {
              ad_storage: "denied",
              ad_user_data: "denied",
              ad_personalization: "denied",
            });
          }
          if (cookieObj.statistics) {
            gtag("consent", "update", {
              analytics_storage: "granted",
            });
            dataLayer.push({ event: "truendo_cc_statistics" });
            _hsq.push(['doNotTrack', {track: true}]); // Enable Hubspot tracking
          } else {
            gtag("consent", "update", {
              analytics_storage: "denied",
            });
            _hsq.push(['doNotTrack']); // Disable Hubspot tracking
          }
          if (cookieObj.social_content) {
            gtag("consent", "update", {
              social_content: "granted",
            });
            dataLayer.push({ event: "truendo_cc_social_content" });
          } else {
            gtag("consent", "update", {
              social_content: "denied",
            });
          }
          if (cookieObj.social_sharing) {
            gtag("consent", "update", {
              social_sharing: "granted",
            });
            dataLayer.push({ event: "truendo_cc_social_sharing" });
          } else {
            gtag("consent", "update", {
              social_sharing: "denied",
            });
          }
        }
        &lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;!-- TRUENDO Privacy Center --&gt;
    &lt;script async="" id="truendoPrivacyPanel" type="text/javascript" src="https://cdn.priv.center/pc/app.pid.js" data-siteid="YOUR WEBSITE ID"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;!-- End TRUENDO Privacy Center --&gt;
    ```
    
    > <div class="sd-callout" data-callout-type="info"><strong>Important Note:</strong> Make Sure that your replace the data-siteid with the one of your domain. You can find your Site ID in the TRUENDO Console. Under the <strong>Banner</strong> section scroll until you see <strong>Integration via script</strong>. You can simply click Copy Site ID</div>
    > 
    > <br />
    > 
    > <br />
    
3.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Remove the </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">async</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">attribute from your </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Hubspot</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">script.</span></span>
4.  <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Add a standard trigger to your </span></span> **<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">Hubspot</span></span>** <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">tag. For example the </span></span> _<span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">All Pages</span></span>_ <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);">trigger.</span></span>

<br />
